                 <table>
                  <tr>
                   <td class="statText">
                    <pre>{50,10,50,10,50,10,50,10,50,10,50,10}</pre>
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                 </table>
                </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                <td class="statText">
                 <pre>Returns: 0.0</pre>
                </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                <td class="statText">
                 <table>
                  <tr>
                   <td class="statText" colspan="2">
                    A weighting of -1,0,0,1,1 predicts price correctly every time (in the past). 
   For example, the prediction of the most recent price is 
   -1*50 + 0*10 + 0*50 + 1*10 + 1*50 = 10 which was exactly right.
                   </td>
                  </tr>
                 </table>
                </td>
               </tr>
              </table>
             </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
             <td align="center" class="statText" nowrap="true">
              2)
             </td>
